00:25:39.040 --> 00:25:45.330
and where can we take
these two characters?

00:25:45.330 --> 00:25:46.290
Brits have a saying.

00:25:46.290 --> 00:25:48.640
They say, don't
treat me like a dog.

00:25:48.640 --> 00:25:50.750
I'll act like a dog.

00:25:50.750 --> 00:25:57.040
So if they treat women
in the right way,

00:25:57.040 --> 00:26:00.160
if they give them
the key positions

00:26:00.160 --> 00:26:06.795
in huge industrial places,
or industry, Hollywood,

00:26:06.795 --> 00:26:11.770
the American film industry, we
see more and more female leads,

00:26:11.770 --> 00:26:15.920
not only in TV series, but also
in films that may be villains

00:26:15.920 --> 00:26:17.800
or may be angels.

00:26:17.800 --> 00:26:24.580
But it all depends on how women,
how we are doing in our real

00:26:24.580 --> 00:26:30.270
lives in real society that
could be depicted and shown

00:26:30.270 --> 00:26:31.610
on the silver screen.

00:26:31.610 --> 00:26:35.820
It all depends on us, and we are
doing a great job, I believe.

00:26:35.820 --> 00:26:38.780
I mean, everywhere women
are doing their best.

00:26:38.780 --> 00:26:41.770
Even in Saudi Arabia,
finally, finally, they

00:26:41.770 --> 00:26:43.560
got their right to vote.

00:26:43.560 --> 00:26:45.890
So we are at the
very beginning of it.

00:26:45.890 --> 00:26:48.990
You won't believe how late
some countries have given

00:26:48.990 --> 00:26:50.870
the rights to women to vote.

00:26:50.870 --> 00:26:53.130
It's unbelievable.

00:26:53.130 --> 00:26:55.880
So we're at the very
beginning of it,

00:26:55.880 --> 00:27:00.750
but the equality of
genders is under way soon.

00:27:00.750 --> 00:27:04.240
We have already gotten
there, but we still

00:27:04.240 --> 00:27:09.300
need to talk about it, and
make other people, especially

00:27:09.300 --> 00:27:12.780
the countries under
development, understand

00:27:12.780 --> 00:27:17.720
the importance of women's
role in a society, that really

00:27:17.720 --> 00:27:20.650
women and men, they're
not that much different.

00:27:20.650 --> 00:27:25.860
They can both be helpful and
profitable to their societies.

00:27:25.860 --> 00:27:30.160
But we need more strong
females, and you are right.

00:27:30.160 --> 00:27:35.720
And maybe it's because
there are still

00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:40.500
male leads who bring more people
to the theaters than females,

00:27:40.500 --> 00:27:42.060
especially in the far east.

00:27:42.060 --> 00:27:43.850
And this is unbelievable.

00:27:43.850 --> 00:27:46.740
Sometimes, when people
talk about the inequality

00:27:46.740 --> 00:27:50.200
of receiving salary
here in our industry,

00:27:50.200 --> 00:27:54.790
some women say they
receive less than men.

00:27:54.790 --> 00:27:57.320
I truly believe it's
not about gender.

00:27:57.320 --> 00:27:59.080
It's not about
because we are women.

00:27:59.080 --> 00:27:59.700
They are men.

00:27:59.700 --> 00:28:02.840
It's because they bring more
people to thee theaters,

00:28:02.840 --> 00:28:05.950
especially when it
goes to the far east

00:28:05.950 --> 00:28:09.020
or the Middle
East, or east east.

00:28:09.020 --> 00:28:12.080
It seems like
there's still actors

00:28:12.080 --> 00:28:15.730
who bringing people to the
theaters rather than actresses.

00:28:15.730 --> 00:28:17.920
But that will change soon.

00:28:17.920 --> 00:28:18.753
AUDIENCE: I hope so.

00:28:18.753 --> 00:28:21.630
Do you think-- Sorry,
for [INAUDIBLE]

00:28:21.630 --> 00:28:23.850
but do you think there's
this kind of the thing,

00:28:23.850 --> 00:28:27.960
that some things, the
femininity of a political power,

00:28:27.960 --> 00:28:30.580
scares some people,
especially scares

00:28:30.580 --> 00:28:33.780
some men who feel threatened?

00:28:33.780 --> 00:28:36.150
I mean, your examples
that you came up,

00:28:36.150 --> 00:28:39.920
they were strong women, but I
mean, Merkel, Angela Merkel,

00:28:39.920 --> 00:28:42.080
wasn't on your list.

00:28:42.080 --> 00:28:45.610
I mean, she doesn't seem to
bring some of her femininity

00:28:45.610 --> 00:28:48.720
into her governance.

00:28:48.720 --> 00:28:51.030
SHOHREH AGHDASHLOO: We
all try not to do that.

00:28:51.030 --> 00:28:54.270
I mean, now I'm joining
you in this one,

00:28:54.270 --> 00:28:58.210
because when you were
carrying a key position,

00:28:58.210 --> 00:29:00.110
people do respect you a lot.

00:29:00.110 --> 00:29:03.180
You don't want to mix it
up with your femininity.

00:29:03.180 --> 00:29:06.500
You don't want people to respect
you because you're a woman.

00:29:06.500 --> 00:29:09.080
Oh, look at you, because
you have nice hair.

00:29:09.080 --> 00:29:12.860
On the contrary, you tuck the
hair back, try to wear suits.

00:29:12.860 --> 00:29:14.690
Why do you think we
wear suits all the time

00:29:14.690 --> 00:29:16.140
when we go to meetings?

00:29:16.140 --> 00:29:20.270
Because we're trying to
say that I am like you.

00:29:20.270 --> 00:29:21.600
I'm not different.

00:29:21.600 --> 00:29:23.770
I'm not necessarily a woman.

00:29:23.770 --> 00:29:28.560
I'm not proud of my
hair or my figure.

00:29:28.560 --> 00:29:30.370
I'm here because
I'm a human being,

00:29:30.370 --> 00:29:32.579
because I love my
profession, I love my job.

00:29:32.579 --> 00:29:35.120
Because I'm here because I want
to talk to you about this job

00:29:35.120 --> 00:29:40.110
and see what we can do
to make it even better.

00:29:40.110 --> 00:29:43.360
That's why we try not
to even-- I sometimes

00:29:43.360 --> 00:29:47.410
forget I'm a woman, especially
with this thick voice,

00:29:47.410 --> 00:29:50.590
and especially when I call,
some people say, sir, hold on.

00:29:50.590 --> 00:29:51.690
And I'm like, yes.

00:29:51.690 --> 00:29:52.646
I will hold on.

00:29:52.646 --> 00:29:55.220
I'm happy they called me a sir.

00:29:55.220 --> 00:29:56.980
British embassy, all the time.

00:29:56.980 --> 00:29:59.126
Every time I call to ask
for a visa for my mother,

00:29:59.126 --> 00:30:00.500
they're like, sir,
hold the line.

00:30:00.500 --> 00:30:02.002
I'm holding.

00:30:02.002 --> 00:30:03.640
I'm happy they called me a sir.

00:30:03.640 --> 00:30:04.347
So yeah.

00:30:04.347 --> 00:30:05.430
AUDIENCE: Thank very much.

00:30:05.430 --> 00:30:06.763
SHOHREH AGHDASHLOO: My pleasure.

00:30:08.730 --> 00:30:11.410
AUDIENCE: So now that
you've finished your book,

00:30:11.410 --> 00:30:14.210
you're creating
something of your own,

00:30:14.210 --> 00:30:18.010
do you have any interest
in going behind the camera

00:30:18.010 --> 00:30:20.450
or doing any writing
in the future?

00:30:20.450 --> 00:30:23.820
SHOHREH AGHDASHLOO: You just
asked the best question ever.

00:30:23.820 --> 00:30:24.400
I'm dying.

00:30:24.400 --> 00:30:26.290
I'm dying to direct.

00:30:26.290 --> 00:30:29.010
And I think I can do a good job.

00:30:29.010 --> 00:30:30.780
I love acting.

00:30:30.780 --> 00:30:33.150
I love teaching it.

00:30:33.150 --> 00:30:34.960
As a matter of fact,
my second book,

00:30:34.960 --> 00:30:37.670
the one after this one, which
I'm working on right now,

00:30:37.670 --> 00:30:39.920
is purely about acting.

00:30:39.920 --> 00:30:41.310
It's all technical.

00:30:41.310 --> 00:30:44.140
I want to teach
youngsters who would

00:30:44.140 --> 00:30:47.360
like to become actors
stuff that they do not

00:30:47.360 --> 00:30:50.330
learn in colleges, not
in the universities,

00:30:50.330 --> 00:30:56.190
not until you start working,
and you learn it by experience.

00:30:56.190 --> 00:30:57.940
That's why I love to teach it.

00:30:57.940 --> 00:31:00.080
I love to interact with actors.

00:31:00.080 --> 00:31:03.040
I try to do that all the
time, every time I'm working.

00:31:03.040 --> 00:31:05.080
And sometimes, they come to me.

00:31:05.080 --> 00:31:08.110
They ask me, and I
try to do my best.

00:31:08.110 --> 00:31:10.996
So I'm trying to act, to direct.

00:31:10.996 --> 00:31:13.540
I would love, love,
love to direct.

00:31:13.540 --> 00:31:14.670
And who knows?

00:31:14.670 --> 00:31:16.690
Maybe I'll start with "Expanse."

00:31:16.690 --> 00:31:17.970
I've already talked about it.

00:31:17.970 --> 00:31:20.210
And some of them like the idea.

00:31:20.210 --> 00:31:22.440
They were like, oh, we
should pitch it to so and so.

00:31:22.440 --> 00:31:24.390
And I was like, go pitch it.

00:31:24.390 --> 00:31:26.635
Go do whatever you can do.

00:31:26.635 --> 00:31:28.170
Pitch it as soon as you can.

00:31:28.170 --> 00:31:30.700
I'm dying to direct
one of these episodes.

00:31:30.700 --> 00:31:31.240
Yeah?

00:31:31.240 --> 00:31:34.150
That's what I'm hoping to do.

00:31:34.150 --> 00:31:36.630
Working with actors.

